# Testing Patterns

## Framework

pytest with `httpx` (`TestClient`). In-memory SQLite for isolation.

## Fixtures (conftest.py)

```python
@pytest.fixture()
def db():
    engine = create_engine("sqlite:///:memory:", connect_args={"check_same_thread": False}, poolclass=StaticPool)
    Base.metadata.create_all(bind=engine)
    session = sessionmaker(bind=engine)()
    yield session
    session.close()

@pytest.fixture()
def client(db):
    app.dependency_overrides[get_db] = lambda: (yield db)
    with TestClient(app) as c:
        yield c
    app.dependency_overrides.clear()

@pytest.fixture()
def paired_client(db, client):
    user = User(name="TestUser")
    db.add(user); db.commit(); db.refresh(user)
    db.add(Device(token="test-token", user_id=user.id, label="Test", client_ip_last="127.0.0.1"))
    db.commit()
    client.cookies.set(DEVICE_COOKIE_NAME, "test-token")
    return client, user
```

## Test Conventions

- `client` for guest tests, `paired_client` for authenticated tests
- Mock external services with `@patch`
- Assert on `resp.json()` shape, DB state, and status codes
- Test both guest and paired user paths
- Test files named `test_*.py` matching the module they test

## Test Coverage Areas

| Area | Test Files |
|------|-----------|
| Core API | `test_api.py`, `test_conversations.py` |
| Trading | `test_trading.py`, `test_scanner_scoring.py`, `test_position_sizing.py`, `test_market_data.py` |
| Brokers | `test_broker_service.py`, `test_broker_sync.py`, `test_trades_sync.py` |
| AI/LLM | `test_openai_routing.py`, `test_provider_selection.py`, `test_fallback_parser.py` |
| Brain | `test_code_agent.py`, `test_memory.py`, `test_personality.py` |
| Features | `test_planner_schema.py`, `test_projects.py`, `test_intercom.py`, `test_voice.py` |

## Running Tests

```bash
pytest tests/ -v
pytest tests/test_scanner_scoring.py -v -k "test_specific"
```
